# 🛒 Online Store – Java Console Application

This is a Java-based console application developed as part of an Advanced 
Programming course project at the University of Isfahan. The project 
simulates an online store system with support for multiple user roles and 
modular product management, inspired by real-world platforms like Digikala 
and Amazon.

## 🚀 Features

- Role-based user system (Customer, Seller, Admin)
- Product management with category-specific attributes
- Shopping cart and invoice generation
- Review and rating system (only for verified buyers)
- Admin panel for approval and moderation
- Extendable code architecture using OOP principles

## 🧑‍💻 Technologies Used

- Language: Java (JDK 8+)
- Structure: Multi-package with `src/com/company/` hierarchy
- Version Control: Git
- Interface: Command-line (menu-based)


## 📌 Notes

- This project is **Phase 1** of a multi-phase build and is structured for 
scalability.
- Future phases will add persistence, UI, and multi-user interactions.

